Table of contents:
==================
1. untar installfile
2. configure settings
3. start database
4. install

####################################################################

1. untar installfile
====================
untar the installfile named reporting.tar.bz2 with the folloing command

tar -xjvf reporting.tar.bz2

for the following steps change to the directory you untared the bz2-file

####################################################################

2. configure settings
=====================
To configure your application open the file arco_install.settings. The configureable values are:

ARCO_VERSION          Version of the last application installed. This is needed to unregister the old application.
COMMON_PATH           the absolute rootpath to store files from the application
QUERIES               subdirectory of COMMON_PATH to store your queries
RESULTS               subdirectory of COMMON_PATH to store your results
VIEWCONFIGURATIONS    subdirectory of COMMON_PATH to store your viewconfigurations
DBPRODNAME            name of the database containing data of production
DBPROJNAME            name of the database containing data of queries, results and viewconfiguration
DBHOST                name of the host the database is running i.e dbserver.tamplate.local
DBPORT                port the database is listening to. dedfault is 5432
DBUSER                user with a least readaccess to the database containing data of production
DBPWD                 encrypted password of the DBUSER. (To encrypt the password see below.)

2a. encrypt password of database user
=====================================
./dbpwd -e <password of dbuser>

####################################################################

3. start database
=================
Start the database if not already running. The database must be started before the applicationserver
will be started. Otherwise the application may not connect to the database.

####################################################################

4. install
==========
To install the application make sure to be the root user and call
./arco_install

While running the script an older version will be deregistered, the application will be installed and
registered and the applicationserver will be restarted.

############################ - EOF - ###############################
